The paper focuses on building multimodal conversation systems using deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CL and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes new sub-tasks and evaluation methodologies, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. The paper also presents neural models and establishes baseline performance, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges and complexities involved in each dialog state, which involves information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR a likely sub-category.
